-- Tiger Woods Holds One-Shot Lead in Opening Round of British Open
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-07-19T10:36:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-19/tiger-woods-holds-one-shot-lead-in-opening-round-of-british-open.html
Tiger Woods , seeking his first major
title in four years, holds a one-stroke lead in the opening
round of the British Open.  Woods is 4 under par through seven holes at Royal Lytham &
St. Annes in Lancashire, England. The 14-time major winner has
moved in front with consecutive birdies on the sixth and seventh
holes.  Masters champion Bubba Watson and Adam Scott are tied for
second at 3 under, with former major winners Paul Lawrie, Zach
Johnson and Graeme McDowell at 2 under.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  